The paper deals with a graph optimization problem, specifically finding a 2-edge connected spanning subgraph of minimum cost. This falls under the category of graph algorithms and optimization, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as it covers graph algorithms and optimization. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as it covers combinatorial optimization problems. cs.GT (Graph Theory) is another possible category as it covers the study of graphs and their properties. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) are less likely but still possible categories as they cover the analysis of algorithms and optimization problems.
